Britam has for the fifth time in a row sponsored the annual Guineas horse racing challenge set to take place on Sunday at the Ngong Racecourse. Britam Group director of marketing and corporate affairs Dr. Muthoga Ngera donated Sh3 million as sponsorship for this year’s event, pushing up the total amount donated to over Sh15 million in support the Jockey Club since the inaugural Britam Kenya Guineas in 2015. He said Britam Kenya Guineas race day has grown in popularity to become a premier day in the horse racing calendar. “The attendance has increased from an average of 1,500 people in 2015 to 5,000 people in 2017 and has attracted top international teams from South Africa, Mauritius, Zimbabwe to compete for the top prizes,” he noted.